content.description: Start on the first of two detached blocks on the left side of the south face. Foloow slopers to a good hand jam and drift rightward into intense pocket pulling to a crux near the gently overhanging arete. Classic pockets!
content.location: On the south face of the 4th house boulder(last as one hikes up the trail). Traverse left to right finishing on the corner. This face has a host of tall problems.

content.description: Climb up the center of the east face using anything in reach. the crux is the obvious blank section in the middle of the problem. This is a classic problem on par with the Jesus Boulder. (Pics to come soon)
content.protection: 3 pads is pimp, but bring more if you got'em.
content.location: Located on the first of the House boulders as one hikes up the trail. The east face hosts a couple of excellent routes which should be on any highballer's list.

content.description: Climb up the central buldge on the east face of house boulder#3. Great pocket pulling leads one to big jugs and big air potential. Classic!
content.location: Located on the east face of the fourth house boulder as one is hiking up the trail.

content.description: Located in between the #2 & #3 House Bouklders is a corridor which has a number of new problems on both walls. The lines are tall committing as well as a couple of 40+ft traverses which are great!
Very large blocks with fun and tall lines.  Have spotters on alert when climbing here.
